# ðŸŽ¥ Transcoding Reporter

Automated reporting system for video transcoding jobs.  
It fetches data from **Drive** and **WAC configs**, generates reports (HTML + CSV), and sends them via **AWS SES**.

---

## ðŸš€ Features
- Generates **summary + detailed table** for transcoding jobs.
- Sends **email reports** with HTML body (last 50 items) and CSV attachment (all items).
- Supports **interval-based scheduling** (every N minutes/hours/days) or **cron-style fixed times**.
- Provides REST API for monitoring and manual triggers.
- Dockerized for easy deployment.

---

## ðŸ“¡ API Endpoints

### 1. Get Email Recipients
```http
GET /emails


2. Add Email Recipients / BCC
POST /emails/add
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "recipients": ["new@example.com"],
  "bcc": ["manager@example.com"]
}

3. Remove Email Recipients / BCC
POST /emails/remove
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "recipients": ["user@example.com"],
  "bcc": ["manager@example.com"]
}

4. Report Page (Browser View)
GET /report


Opens an HTML report page in the browser, showing:

Total counts (In-Queue, Success, Failed)

Full searchable/filterable table (last 3 months)


# Report page (HTML)
curl http://192.168.51.238:4000/report

# Get recipients
curl http://192.168.51.238:4000/emails

curl -X POST https://tsc-report.pve.mogiio.com/emails/add \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"recipients":["anilchauhan@mogiio.com", "waqas.qazi@mogiio.com"]}'


  
# Add recipient
curl -X POST http://192.168.51.238:4000/emails/add \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"recipients":["test@example.com"]}'

# Remove recipient
curl -X POST http://192.168.51.238:4000/emails/remove \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"recipients":["test@example.com"]}'
